radiographic_examinations.findings: Initial AIMS score: 2.4; Various scores recorded over time indicate fluctuations in tardive dyskinesia severity.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Scores improved from 2.4 at week 0 to 1.1 at week 14, then worsened after discontinuation of reserpine, peaking at 3.2 by week 39.
